Emma Jayne wrote a review Mar 8
Birmingham, United Kingdom17 contributions
Far from a retreat!
If you like the nicer hotels in life, do not book here. DO NOT be fooled by the nice photographs online. If you do want to take a chance (which is likely as you’ll skim over this review believing this hotel is 5 star/5 bubbles and ignore the few poor ratings like we did) then be very careful with choosing your room type. There appears to be two types of accommodation - the main building where reception is located; a miserable concrete block of flats and then villas throughout the rest of the grounds which are obviously newer additions. We were in a ‘sunlit suite with sea view’ and whilst the room was spacious, it lacked any sort of style and was extremely basic. The view, albeit as promised, resembled a graveyard of some kind and was not the lush green manicured grounds you’d…
Date of stay: March 2024
This review is the subjective opinion of a Tripadvisor member and not of Tripadvisor LLC. Tripadvisor performs checks on reviews as part of our industry-leading trust & safety standards. Read our transparency report to learn more.
