Naman Retreat perfect place to relax
We ended this year's Asia trip with a 10 day relaxing stay at Naman retreat. This was our 2nd stay at this resort/the first in 2017, which we had wonderful memories of/. Already the airport transfer provided by limousine from the hotel was perfect, The welcome at the reception was warm, friendly smiling Mrs Min from guest relations, she was our personal ambassador. She handles her job perfectly, knows how to relate to guests and was always available to us outside of office hours via what's up. The resort is beautifully maintained, clean, the work of the gardeners is evident at every turn Even after all these years we are still amazed by the size of the Hay Hay restaurant, all made of bamboo poles, spacious , airy, The breakfast buffet offers a wide selection of Western and…
