The perfect retreat for relaxation
My family and I stayed in one of the beachfront villas as we wanted the seaview. Everything was perfect. The villas are clean, modern and spacious. We even had our own pool. Breakfast was superb..a must is the homemade granola. The salad, cheeses, breads etc.was superb too. The Mexican restaurant is a must while here. Especially if you love margaritas and tacos. Our favourite was the ceviche. We also enjoyed the beach bbq. Free flow drinks and superb selection of foods. Plus the singers were really good. There is also a hotel shuttle a few times a day to either DaNang or HoiAn. The hotel is situated in the middle of both towns. The staff at Naman are so friendly and go above and beyond for you. We were looked after by Candy, who messaged us daily to see if we were…
