MAriffin wrote a review Feb 2024
Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia11 contributions
Naman Retreat - good for the soul and mind, so relaxing, so refreshing
Stayed 6 days at the single unit, main building. Has separate living tv area (second tv in room) and kitchenette with fridge, microwave, induction cooker and simple utensils. Nice unit with a balcony and a sofa bed. Bathroom has a tub and separate shower, quite spacious. Swimming pool is on ground floor outside the lobby area - so convenient. Another pool is by the beach next to the restaurant. Hotel is located in-between Hoi An and Da Nang, easy to get Grab - just use the app. Love walking around the area under the trees - so cooling. Beach sand is soft, view is nice for sunrise. For more luxurious stay, try the villa. Easy to get to Hue (2.5 hours away), Da Nang (about 30 mins away) , Ba Na Hills and Hoi An (about 25 mins away) from here.
Dear valued guest, Thank you for your recent stay at Naman Retreat and providing us with your valuable feedback. We are happy to know that you had an enjoyable stay with us. Your comments on the service provided by our staff are most gratifying and will be shared with the whole team. It was certainly a pleasure for us to be at your service and we all look forward to welcoming you again soon to Naman Retreat Warm regards, Thao Pham Front Office Manager
